1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
Science has a clearer story about transcription factors than social media does.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:10,800
Transcription factors are proteins that bind to specific DNA sequences, turning genes on or off.

3
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:17,600
Imagine them as the conductors of an orchestra, controlling the symphony of life at a molecular level.

4
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:22,800
Research shows that dysregulation of these factors can lead to diseases like cancer.

5
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:28,400
So next time you think about your health, remember these tiny but mighty proteins.

6
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,400
